\layout Chapter

Introduction
\layout Section

Abstract
\layout Standard

This document describes a XML document format that can be used to import
 / export database schemas using Druid.
 Even though this specification can be used to describe a generic database
 schema, the reader should be at least familiar with basic Druid concepts.
 See the 
\noun on 
druid essentials
\noun default 
 manual for a reference.
\layout Section

The need
\layout Standard

Even though a Druid project is stored in XML format, this format cannot
 be easily used to import / export database schemas.
 The problems are:
\layout Enumerate

To use the project file format a DTD should be available.
 Because this file format follows every Druid's enhancement it is very dynamic
 so keeping the DTD updated can be difficult and error prone.
\layout Enumerate

The format contains internal Druid stuff that should be avoided.
\layout Enumerate

The format itself is not suited for an easy import / export.
 There are attributes, like serials, that are difficult to handle and don't
 need to be present in a general import / export format.
\layout Standard

Given these problems, what we need is a XML file format that:
\layout Enumerate

Is easy to generate / import,
\layout Enumerate

Is independent from the project file format,
\layout Enumerate

Has a simple DTD.
